[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Domain accuracy validation:**
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Case-mix adjustment using O/E ratios: Standard methodology in provider profiling (used by CMS, most commercial payers)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - HCC risk scores for case-mix adjustment: Correct and standard (CMS-HCC is the dominant risk adjustment model)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Minimum panel size 30-50 for primary care: Consistent with published literature on statistical reliability of provider metrics
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - K-Means with K=3-5 for provider segmentation: Appropriate starting point; the recipe correctly notes that provider data rarely produces clean separation
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Silhouette scores 0.25-0.45: Realistic for provider profiling (published studies report similar ranges)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Quarterly refresh cadence: Standard for provider profiling (practice patterns are stable over months)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - 70-80% cluster stability quarter-over-quarter: Realistic and consistent with published provider profiling studies
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Winsorization at 2.5 standard deviations: Standard approach for handling extreme O/E ratios
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - PCA reduction to 5-8 components from 15-25 metrics: Appropriate dimensionality reduction for this domain
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - The distinction between hard assignments (K-Means) and soft assignments (GMM) is correctly drawn and the recommendation to use soft assignments for feedback conversations is clinically wise
